tion was banned. Many churches were destroyed in the German occupation of Estonia, from 1941 through 1944, and in World War II (1939—1945), and religion was actively persecuted in Estonia under Soviet rule 1944 until 1989, when some measure of tolerance was introduced.</q></ref>. Икеле Кавто Ине Война Эстэнь маласо 80% эрицятне ульть протестантт - лютерант<ref>http://pub.stat.ee/px-web.2001/Dialog/varval.asp?ma=PC0454&lang=1</ref>. 

